caption:
Table 1. Semantic segmentation performance when the model trained on GTA-V dataset is adapted to Cityscapes dataset. We present 
the results of our proposed SISC pseudo-labels based self-supervised learning and PWL augmented self-training. We use the competitive 
baseline model and show a thorough comparison with existing state-of-the-art methods. The abbreviations "ST" and "Adv" indicates the 
self-training (self-supervised learning) and adversarial learning respectively.

Table 2. Semantic segmentation performance of Cityscapes validation set when adapted from SYNTHIA dataset. We present mIoU and 
mIoU* (13-categories) comparison with existing state-of-the-art methods for Cityscapes validation set.

Table 3. Performance (mIoU, mIoU*) gain comparison between 
the GTA-V and SYNTHIA trained source models and the respec-
tive adapted models from GTA-V and SYNTHIA to Cityscapes.
Table 4. Influence of λF cl and η on overall performance.
